  },
  "type": "spell",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>This spell lets you convince a snake that you mean it no harm. Choose a snake that you can see within range. It must see and hear you. If the snake's Intelligence is 4 or higher, the spell fails. Otherwise, the snake must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or be charmed by you for the spell's duration. If you or one of your companions harms the target, the spell ends.</p><p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, you can affect one additional snake for each slot level above 1st.</p>",
